ADDITIONAL TERMS — PROHIBITED USES

The following uses are explicitly prohibited regardless of any other
provision of this licence:

1. Military use. Use of this software, or any derivative work, by any
   military organisation, armed force, defence contractor, or any entity
   whose primary purpose includes armed conflict or weapons development,
   of any nation.

2. Intelligence and surveillance use. Use of this software, or any
   derivative work, by any intelligence agency, signals intelligence
   organisation, state surveillance apparatus, law enforcement agency
   conducting mass surveillance, or any entity whose primary purpose
   includes the covert collection, analysis, or exploitation of personal
   data without the explicit, informed, and ongoing consent of the
   individuals concerned.

3. This prohibition applies equally to all nations, governments, and
   non-state actors without exception.

Rationale: THRIVES exists to support people processing trauma. That
data must not become an instrument of surveillance, warfare, or
coercion. This clause exists to make that impossible, not merely
against policy.
